{{Quick Guide}}

==Details==
{{Quest details page|Zogre Flesh Eaters}}

==Walkthrough==
===Starting off===
{{Checklist|
*Speak to [[Grish]] located in [[Jiggig]] west of the [[Gu'Tanoth]] and south of [[Castle Wars]] (east of [[Fairy rings|fairy ring]] {{Fairycode|bkp}}) and offer to help. {{Chat option|2What do you mean sickies?|4Can I help in any way?|2Okay, I'll check things out and report back.|1Yes, I'm really sure!}}
''Grish will give you two [[Super restore potion]]s and three [[Cooked chompy|Cooked chompy birds]].''
*Speak to [[Ogre guard]] to the east, he will remove the barricade to gain access to the Zogre-infested area.
*Climb over the crushed barricade and run east to a set of stairs going downwards, go down these stairs.
}}

===The cave===
'''''Note:''' You may now (or already have been) become diseased if under 89 combat and a [[Zogre]] or [[Skogre]] attacks you (level 44). '''Carry [[Super restore potion]]s at all times.''' The [[disease]] lowers a random skill 10 levels every minute or so!''
{{Checklist|
*Run north-west to an area with a blackened floor, a short cut scene will begin.
*Search the [[skeleton]] next to the [[Broken Lecturn]]. A [[Zombie (Zogre Flesh Eaters)|Zombie]] will appear and attack, kill it to obtain the [[Ruined backpack]].
*Open the [[Ruined backpack]] to obtain a [[Dragon inn tankard]], some [[rotten food]] and a [[knife]].
*Search the broken lecturn for the [[Torn page]] (make sure you keep this).
*Attempt to search the [[coffin]] west of the [[Skeleton]], and then use a [[knife]] on it.
*Attempt to open coffin (may take a couple of tries), search the coffin for the [[Black prism]].
}}
===Yanille===
{{Checklist|*Go to the Dragon Inn in [[Yanille]] and use the tankard on the bartender. The [[Minigame Teleport]] to [[NMZ]] can take you here quickly.
*Speak to [[Zavistic Rarve]] in the [[Wizards' Guild]] in [[Yanille]] (if you don't have the required level to enter, ring the bell out front). ({{Chat option|1I'm here about the sicks…err Zogres}} if you have started [[Hand in the Sand]])}}
===Incriminating Sithik===
{{Checklist|
*Speak to [[Sithik Ints]] in his bed in the upstairs bedroom in the guest house north of the [[Wizards' Guild]] {{Chat option|3Do you mind if I look around?}}
*Search the drawers, cupboard and wardrobe for [[Book of portraiture]], [[Necromancy book]], [[Papyrus]], [[Charcoal]] and a [[Book of 'h.a.m'|Book of 'H.A.M']].
*Read all three books.
*Use all three books on [[Sithik Ints|Sithik]].
*Use [[Papyrus]] on Sithik.
*Use [[Sithik portrait|portrait]] on Sithik.
**'''Note:''' He must appreciate the "honesty" of the portrait, not the "truth". More [[papyrus]] can be found in the drawers.
**'''Note:''' The portrait's examine text must say "A classic realist charcoal portrait of Sithik."
*Go to the [[Dragon Inn]] in [[Yanille]] and use the Dragon Inn Tankard, then the [[Sithik portrait|portrait]] on the Bartender.
}}
''The Bartender will [[signed portrait|sign the portrait]] as an affidavit.''
{{Checklist|
*Speak to [[Zavistic Rarve]] while holding the [[Necromancy book]], [[Book of 'h.a.m'|Book of 'H.A.M']], the tankard and the [[Sithik portrait|signed portrait]]. {{Chat option|3I have some items that I'd like you to look at.}} or {{Chat option|1I'm here about the sicks…err Zogres}{Chat option|3I have some items that I'd like you to look at.}} if you have started [[Hand in the Sand]].
}}
''[[Zavistic Rarve]] will give you a [[Strange potion]].''
{{Checklist|
*Use the [[Strange potion]] on the [[Cup of tea]] on top of [[Sithik Ints|Sithik's]] drawers.
*Go downstairs and back upstairs.
*Speak to [[Sithik Ints|Sithik]], obtain answers to all three questions in order to make [[Relicym's balm]] and [[Brutal arrows]] {{Chat option|1How do I remove the effects of the spell from the area?|2How do I get rid of the undead ogres|3How do I get rid of the disease|4Sorry, I have to go.}}.
}}
===Relocating the ceremonial grounds===
{{Checklist|*Return and speak to [[Grish]] {{Chat option|1I found who's responsible for the Zogres being here.|}}. He will give you an Ogre gate key to access the Ceremonial chamber.
*Talk to Grish again ''"There must be an easier way to kill these [[Zogre]]s" ''to learn how to equip [[Composite ogre bow]]s {{Chat option|2|}}.
*Prepare to fight [[Slash Bash]] (level 111). If you are using an [[comp ogre bow]] instead of [[Crumble Undead]], follow the "optional" steps below.}}

=== Making an ogre composite bow (optional) ===
{{Checklist|*Chop an [[Achey Tree]] for logs.
*Use a knife on the achey tree logs with [[wolf bones]] in your inventory, and select option 2 to create an unstrung comp bow.
*String the bow with [[bow string]] to create the finished bow. 
}}

=== Making Relicym's balm (optional) ===
{{Checklist|
*Either buy one from the Grand Exchange or make it yourself by adding [[Rogue's purse]] to a [[Vial of water]] and then add [[Snake weed]]. It is not needed for the quest but giving it to [[Uglug Nar]] will allow you to purchase [[Relicym's balm]] from his shop if needed in the future.
}}
===Making brutal arrows (optional)===
'''''Note:''' If you have access to the Grand Exchange, you can just buy the arrows and skip this section.''
{{Checklist|
*Cut down [[Achey Tree]]s for [[Achey tree logs]].
*[[Fletch]] the [[Achey tree logs|logs]] with a [[knife]] into [[Ogre arrow shaft]]s.
*Add [[feather]]s to the [[Ogre arrow shaft|shafts]].
*With a [[hammer]] in your inventory use [[nails]] on the [[Flighted ogre arrow]]s.
}}
===Fighting Slash Bash===
'''''Note: '''[[Slash Bash]] uses [[Ranged]] and [[Melee]], easiest method is to use Ranged from a [[safespot]] with [[Protect from Ranged]] [[prayer]] turned on. Alternatively, one may use the spell Crumble Undead if they prefer to use magic.''
{{Checklist|
*Head back down into [[Jiggig]].
*Travel west until you reach two sets of doors.
*Go through both doors and go down the stairs.
*Follow the chamber to the end and search the stand.
*Kill [[Slash Bash]] and collect the [[Zogre bones]] and [[Ogre artefact]] that he drops.
*Return and speak to [[Grish]]. {{Chat option|1}}
**You can now sell the [[Black prism]] to [[Zavistic Rarve]] for 2000 coins or [[Yanni Salika]] for 5000 coins, after the quest.}}
'''Congratulations! Quest Complete!'''

